## Example Docker Compose Files

The following examples are simplified versions of the compose files currently used in the homelab.

### Plex

```yaml
services:
  plex:
    image: lscr.io/linuxserver/plex:latest
    container_name: plex
    restart: unless-stopped

    network_mode: host

    environment:
      - PUID=1000
      - PGID=1000
      - TZ=Europe/Rome

    volumes:
      - /mnt/SERVERDATA/appdata/plex:/config
      - /mnt/SERVERDATA/media:/media
```

---

### Duplicati

```yaml
services:
  duplicati:
    image: lscr.io/linuxserver/duplicati:latest
    container_name: duplicati
    restart: unless-stopped

    ports:
      - "8200:8200"

    environment:
      - PUID=1000
      - PGID=1000
      - TZ=Europe/Rome
      - SETTINGS_ENCRYPTION_KEY=<redacted>

    volumes:
      - /mnt/SERVERDATA/appdata/duplicati:/config
      - /mnt/SERVERDATA:/source
      - /mnt/SERVERDATA/backups:/backups
```

---

### Nextcloud

```yaml
services:
  nextcloud:
    image: nextcloud:latest
    container_name: nextcloud
    restart: unless-stopped

    ports:
      - "8080:80"

    volumes:
      - /mnt/SERVERDATA/appdata/nextcloud:/var/www/html
      - /mnt/SERVERDATA/data:/data
```

---

### Home Assistant

```yaml
services:
  homeassistant:
    image: ghcr.io/home-assistant/home-assistant:stable
    container_name: homeassistant
    restart: unless-stopped

    network_mode: host

    volumes:
      - /mnt/SERVERDATA/appdata/homeassistant:/config

    environment:
      - TZ=Europe/Rome
```
